The paper focuses on developing a deep learning method for visual servoing in unstructured and occluded environments, specifically in the context of robotic crop harvesting. This falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for the deep learning approach suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the method to improve the view of occluded fruit in a protected cropping environment suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
